== Romanian ==
=== Adjective ===
'''gata'''

#[[finished]], [[ready]].

=== Etymology ===
Via a pre-Roman language, from Proto-Indo-European ''*gwm.t-io-<*gwem-'', "to go, come". Has an Albanian [[cognate]], ''[[gat]], [[gati]]'', as well as common Slavonic and Sanskrit cognates, etc.

